        <p>Italian geologist and palaeontologist. Graduated at Padua, 1875; studied at Paris and Monaco. Professor of natural history at Padua, 1880. With Giovanni Canestrini, translated <hi rend="italic">Expression</hi> into Italian (1878). Professor of geology, University of Naples, 1887–1916.</p></note>
